---
title: Charred Corn Elote Bowls with Farro, Spiced Pepitas, and Chipotle-Lime Dressing
description: Eating Mexican street corn is our favorite way to feel summer vibes all year round. No matter the weather, one bite of this tasty bowl will make everything feel a whole lot sunnier. In this twist on Mexican elote, corn on the cob is charred on the stovetop to develop a smoky-sweet flavor, then the kernels are piled atop lime-spiked farro along with smoky caramelized pepitas, arugula, radishes, and Monterey Jack cheese. To tie it all together, it’s drizzled with an addictive chipotle-lime dressing. One bite will have you bowled over.
